The Most Dangerous Man in America: Daniel Ellsberg and the Pentagon Papers;;90;;96;;NC;;This acclaimed documentary provides insight into the actions of Daniel Ellsberg, a leading American military strategist who leaked the Pentagon Papers, a massive top-secret document that pointed to government deception about the Vietnam War. The film looks at Ellsberg himself and at the repercussions of his surprising revelations, which led to a media circus and ultimately contributed to end of both the Vietnam conflict and the presidency of Richard Nixon.;;Documentary;;Judith Ehrlich,Rick Goldsmith;;2009;;Peter Arnett,Ben Bagdikian;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/daniel_ellsberg_doc